31:53.378 --> 31:56.081 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Back to the
campaign.

31:56.114 --> 32:00.719 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Late today, Politico is
reporting the latest
shakeup in Donald Trump's
effort.

32:00.752 --> 32:14.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The national political director
is stepping
down, citing personal reasons.

32:14.566 --> 32:20.071 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The battle for Mosul is the most
important
of the two-year campaign against
ISIS in Iraq,

32:20.105 --> 32:24.309 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and a defeat there would be a
crippling setback
for the extremists.

32:24.342 --> 32:30.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We turn now to a man with
detailed knowledge
of the city and its ethnic and
sectarian crosscurrents.

32:30.949 --> 32:36.655 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Retired General David Petraeus
was in charge
of the 101st Airborne Division
in Mosul in

32:36.688 --> 32:38.523 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
2003.

32:38.557 --> 32:43.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He went on to command the entire
multinational
force in Iraq and also served as
the top general

32:43.929 --> 32:45.697 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for U.S. Central Command.

32:45.730 --> 32:49.734 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He also ran NATO and American
operations in
Afghanistan.

32:49.768 --> 32:55.140 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, from 2011 to 2012, he
served as director
of the CIA.

32:55.173 --> 32:56.608 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He joins me now from New York.

32:56.641 --> 32:58.410 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
General Petraeus, thank you for
being with
us.

32:58.443 --> 33:00.212 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

33:00.245 --> 33:00.579 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID PETRAEUS (RET.), Former
Commander, U.S.
Central Command: Good to be with
you, Judy.

33:00.612 --> 33:02.547 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thank you.

33:02.581 --> 33:07.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, last night at
the debate,
Donald Trump again criticized
the Obama administration

33:07.919 --> 33:13.358 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for telegraphing ahead of time
the plan to
go into Mosul.

33:13.391 --> 33:18.230 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Does Donald Trump have a point
about not letting
the enemy know what you're going
to do?

33:18.263 --> 33:19.965 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

33:19.998 --> 33:23.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID PETRAEUS: What is going on
here is,
in a sense, a distinction
between so-called

33:23.668 --> 33:28.740 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
strategic surprise, which is not
possible
when you're moving tens of
thousands of troops

33:28.773 --> 33:34.813 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and thousands of vehicles and
logistics and
everything else, and then
tactical surprise,

33:34.846 --> 33:40.785 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
which I think probably was
achieved to some
degree when the Iraqi forces
launched the

33:40.819 --> 33:47.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
original operation several days
ago, and actually
has continued, as they have
opened new offensives,

33:47.425 --> 33:53.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
if you will, from the north and
the northeast,
in addition to those in the
initial day, which

33:53.198 --> 33:56.134 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
came from the south and from the
southeast
and east.

33:56.167 --> 34:01.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: How do you see
the challenges
that the Iraqi military and its
allies, including

34:01.139 --> 34:03.208 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the U.S., face in Mosul?

34:03.241 --> 34:04.509 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You know that area well.

34:04.542 --> 34:07.279 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Clearly, it's changed since the
takeover by
ISIS.

34:07.312 --> 34:08.480 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But what do you think they're
confronting?

34:08.513 --> 34:10.315 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

34:10.348 --> 34:14.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID PETRAEUS: Well, first, of
course, they're
confronting what would be a
tough fight in

34:14.419 --> 34:20.025 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a city that's several times
larger than any
that they have cleared so far
over the course

34:20.058 --> 34:25.964 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the last two years, since we
helped them
reconstitute their forces,
reequip, and retrain

34:25.997 --> 34:32.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and remand them, and then as we
have enabled
them so impressively, frankly,
with this armada

34:33.004 --> 34:39.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of manned and unmanned aerial
vehicles, precision-strike
assets and intelligence fusion,
as well as

34:39.945 --> 34:43.281 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
obviously advising and assisting
them.

34:43.315 --> 34:47.085 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they will encounter a tough,
tough city
fight.

34:47.118 --> 34:51.122 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Urban operations are inherently
difficult.

34:51.156 --> 34:56.461 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The enemy has been there for a
couple of years,
has dug tunnel systems, trenches
filled with

34:56.494 --> 34:59.531 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
oil that they will torch to try
to obscure
our optics.

34:59.564 --> 35:01.299 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They will use snipers.

35:01.333 --> 35:05.737 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And every single house, every
single neighborhood
has to be cleared.

35:05.770 --> 35:09.808 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And this is a population that
used to be,
in our day, when I was
privileged to command

35:09.841 --> 35:16.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the 101st Airborne Division, in
Mosul and
Nineveh province, which Mosul
Islamist capital,

35:16.414 --> 35:17.682 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
some two million people.

35:17.716 --> 35:20.719 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's down probably to about 1.2
million now.

35:20.752 --> 35:25.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some of those will leave and go
to the refugees
centers that have been set up to
take care

35:25.123 --> 35:27.292 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of them during the course of the
battle.

35:27.325 --> 35:29.094 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But many will also stay.

35:29.127 --> 35:33.598 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And some will be trapped and
kept there by
the Islamic State, used
essentially as human

35:33.631 --> 35:39.037 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
shields, announcement
complicating factor
for the Iraqi security forces,
the Kurdish

35:39.070 --> 35:43.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Peshmerga, and indeed for our
elements that
are supporting them in this
fight.

35:43.174 --> 35:49.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And I do want to
ask you about
the challenges that the Iraqis
face even assuming

35:49.647 --> 35:51.750 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Mosul is cleared of ISIS.

35:51.783 --> 35:57.188 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first, are you confident
that they will
be able to get ISIS out of
Mosul?

35:57.222 --> 36:00.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And do you think it could take
as long as
a year, which the head of
Central Command

36:00.825 --> 36:01.793 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
has said that it might?

36:01.826 --> 36:03.661 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

36:03.695 --> 36:05.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID PETRAEUS: No, I think --
with respect,
I think he said it could take
months, I think.

36:06.031 --> 36:09.901 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Understandably, he's giving a
bit of the worst-case
analysis.

36:09.934 --> 36:12.404 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's already moving faster than
most predicted.

36:12.437 --> 36:16.708 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have said that, look, the
Islamic State
fighters that are left in Mosul,
maybe as

36:16.741 --> 36:21.279 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
many as 5,000 or 6,000, they
realize that
they are dead men walking.

36:21.312 --> 36:25.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's no question that the
Iraqi security
forces, with all of the enablers
that we're

36:25.850 --> 36:28.420 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
providing them, are going to
clear that city.

36:28.453 --> 36:30.221 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's not in question.

36:30.255 --> 36:35.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The only question is, how long
do the Islamic
State fighters really put up
resistance?

36:35.293 --> 36:41.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are reports already of
substantial numbers
of deserters, many of whom have
been executed,

36:41.099 --> 36:43.435 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and of leaders trying to leave
the city as
well.

36:43.468 --> 36:50.041 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In fact, one of the big
questions that is
out there right now is, where is
Baghdadi,

36:50.075 --> 36:51.876 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the leader of the Islamic State?

36:51.910 --> 36:57.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Is he trapped there with one of
his explosives
experts, or did he actually
escape to the

36:57.115 --> 37:00.185 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
west and try to get back across
the border
to Syria?

37:00.218 --> 37:04.589 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, again, no question that the
Iraqi security
forces will prevail.

37:04.622 --> 37:08.426 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The bigger question is actually
the battle
after this.

37:08.460 --> 37:14.165 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I have made clear in writing
a couple
of months ago, for example, that
the most

37:14.199 --> 37:19.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
complex human terrain in all of
Iraq is to
be found in Mosul and the
province of which

37:19.771 --> 37:23.408 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it is a capital, Nineveh,
biblical Nineveh.

37:23.441 --> 37:27.145 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are Sunni Arabs in the
majority, but
there are also pockets of Shia
Arabs.

37:27.178 --> 37:29.347 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are Turkmen, Sunni as well
as Shia.

37:29.380 --> 37:33.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are Kurds, and they come
from several
political parties that they're
not always

37:33.418 --> 37:35.220 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in agreement with each other.

37:35.253 --> 37:39.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are sizable numbers of
Christians that
were treated horribly under the
Islamic State

37:39.891 --> 37:41.493 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and want to get back to their
areas.

37:41.526 --> 37:42.494 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There are Yazidis.

37:42.527 --> 37:44.262 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There are Shabak.

37:44.295 --> 37:49.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And all of these want to get
back from whence
they came, and they want to play
a part in

37:49.033 --> 37:51.870 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
governance that follows.

37:51.903 --> 37:56.407 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And all will want to be
represented and want
that government to be responsive
to them and

37:56.441 --> 38:01.913 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
guarantee their minority rights,
if they're
not the Sunni Arabs, in addition
to, of course,

38:01.946 --> 38:03.781 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the Sunni Arab majority rule.

38:03.815 --> 38:06.584 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is going to be very, very
difficult.

38:06.618 --> 38:11.222 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We did achieve it early on in
2003, when I
was privileged to command there.

38:11.256 --> 38:13.658 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But we had 28,000 great American
soldiers.

38:13.691 --> 38:16.427 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We had 254 helicopters.

38:16.461 --> 38:21.299 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I had the authority of being
an occupying
commander under the Geneva
Convention, and

38:21.332 --> 38:24.602 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
didn't hesitate, frankly, to use
that authority.

38:24.636 --> 38:28.106 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's no equivalent power
there at this
point in time.

38:28.139 --> 38:34.712 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, this is going to take
intense politics,
intense negotiations and a lot
of individuals

38:34.746 --> 38:38.016 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
undoubtedly demonstrating the
full range of
emotions along the way.

38:38.049 --> 38:42.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
