group Carbon Washington
to put the issue to voters.

42:19.337 --> 42:23.107 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: Initiative 732, it's going
to be on the
November ballot.

42:23.141 --> 42:26.811 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: I-732 works by charging
polluters with
a carbon fee, which lowers
pollution.

42:26.844 --> 42:32.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: And then the revenue that
is created
will go to reducing other taxes
in the state.

42:32.183 --> 42:38.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
